From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 00:13:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fman_pcd: v1.1-A bugfix -- INIT_LIST_HEAD pending_ports in
 fman_pcd_init()

Empirical M2 acceptance-gate verification on 2026-05-25 (kernel
6.18.31-vyos) revealed that patch 0060 forgot to initialise the new
pcd->pending_ports list in fman_pcd_init(), even though it added
the field to struct fman_pcd and used it from
fman_pcd_record_pending_port(),
fman_pcd_install_now_for_existing_ports(), and fman_pcd_release().

Symptom: the new vmlinuz failed to boot on the DUT and never came
back on the network. fman_port_init() runs early during the DPAA
platform probe; the first port hitting the -ENOENT fall-through
(i.e. ask hook not yet registered, which is the whole point of
v1.1-A's retroactive-replay design) called
fman_pcd_record_pending_port() -> list_add_tail(&p->node,
&pcd->pending_ports), and because pcd->pending_ports.next/prev
were zero-initialised by kzalloc, list_add_tail() dereferenced a
NULL pointer -> early kernel panic during platform probe, well
before serial console / network came up. DUT bricked, recovery
required physical serial-console intervention.

This adds the missing INIT_LIST_HEAD adjacent to the other five
existing INIT_LIST_HEAD calls in fman_pcd_init(), so the list is
in valid empty-list state before fman_port_init() can race ahead
of ask_init() on the platform bus.

Acceptance signature: kernel now boots; the rest of the v1.1-A
flow (record -> install_now -> claimed/declined/failed log line)
proceeds as designed in patch 0060.
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
index 128a94e..226f28c 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/fman/fman_pcd.c
@@ -531,6 +531,7 @@ struct fman_pcd *fman_pcd_init(struct fman *fman)
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pcd->manip_profiles);
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pcd->plcr_profiles);
 	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pcd->replic_groups);
+	INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pcd->pending_ports);
 
 	pcd->muram_offset = fman_muram_alloc(muram,
 				     FMAN_PCD_MURAM_RESERVED_BYTES);
-- 
2.39.5
